{
  "video_id": "_2PhFnwj608",
  "title": "Visions of Africa's future, from African filmmakers",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12982.0,
      "end_time": 15633.0,
      "text": "As a child growing up in Nigeria,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15657.0,
      "end_time": 17836.0,
      "text": "books sparked my earliest imagination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19880.0,
      "end_time": 22389.0,
      "text": "but films, films transported me"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23524.0,
      "end_time": 25881.0,
      "text": "to magical places with flying cars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27162.0,
      "end_time": 30436.0,
      "text": "to infinite space with whole universes of worlds to discover."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31413.0,
      "end_time": 34872.0,
      "text": "And my journey of discovery has led to many places and possibilities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34896.0,
      "end_time": 38133.0,
      "text": "all linked with ideas and imagination."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 39213.0,
      "end_time": 41229.0,
      "text": "A decade and a half ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 41253.0,
      "end_time": 44328.0,
      "text": "I moved from working in law and technology in New York"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 44352.0,
      "end_time": 48447.0,
      "text": "to financing, producing and distributing films"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48472.0,
      "end_time": 51179.0,
      "text": "in Nairobi, Lagos and Johannesburg."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 52677.0,
      "end_time": 56236.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve been privileged to see firsthand how in Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 56260.0,
      "end_time": 60147.0,
      "text": "film powerfully explores the marvelous and the mundane,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 61224.0,
      "end_time": 65256.0,
      "text": "how it conveys infinite possibilities and fundamental truths."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 66552.0,
      "end_time": 69910.0,
      "text": "Afrofuturist films like \"Pumzi,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 69115.0,
      "end_time": 73320.0,
      "text": "Wanuri Kahiu&#39;s superb sci-fi flick,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 73560.0,
      "end_time": 77152.0,
      "text": "paint brilliant pictures of Africa&#39;s future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 77176.0,
      "end_time": 80170.0,
      "text": "while Rungano Nyoni&#39;s \"I Am Not A Witch\""
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 80410.0,
      "end_time": 82730.0,
      "text": "and Akin Omotoso&#39;s \"Vaya\""
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 82970.0,
      "end_time": 84857.0,
      "text": "show us and catalogue our present."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 85358.0,
      "end_time": 91410.0,
      "text": "These filmmakers offer nuanced snapshots of Africa&#39;s imagined and lived reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 91650.0,
      "end_time": 95469.0,
      "text": "in contrast to some of the images of Africa that come from outside,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 95493.0,
      "end_time": 98764.0,
      "text": "and the perspectives that accompany all of these images,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 98788.0,
      "end_time": 102192.0,
      "text": "whether sympathetic or dismissive, shape or distort"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 103383.0,
      "end_time": 105000.0,
      "text": "how people see Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 107650.0,
      "end_time": 109328.0,
      "text": "And the truth is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 109352.0,
      "end_time": 111407.0,
      "text": "many people think Africa is screwed up."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 113134.0,
      "end_time": 115554.0,
      "text": "Images play a big part of the reason why."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 119150.0,
      "end_time": 123140.0,
      "text": "Many tropes about Africa persist from pictures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 123380.0,
      "end_time": 126737.0,
      "text": "pictures of famine in Ethiopia 30 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 126761.0,
      "end_time": 129894.0,
      "text": "pictures of the Biafran war half a century ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 131132.0,
      "end_time": 136410.0,
      "text": "But on a continent where the average age is 17,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 136434.0,
      "end_time": 139670.0,
      "text": "these tragic events seem almost prehistoric."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 140168.0,
      "end_time": 142794.0,
      "text": "Their images are far removed"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 142818.0,
      "end_time": 147370.0,
      "text": "from how people in Africa&#39;s many countries see themselves and their neighbors."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 148210.0,
      "end_time": 152890.0,
      "text": "For them, these images do not represent their reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 152113.0,
      "end_time": 154204.0,
      "text": "So what is Africa&#39;s reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 154228.0,
      "end_time": 158725.0,
      "text": "or rather, which of Africa&#39;s many realities do we choose to focus on?"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 159530.0,
      "end_time": 165125.0,
      "text": "Do we accept Emmanuel Macron&#39;s imagination of Africa in 2017"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 165149.0,
      "end_time": 168664.0,
      "text": "as a place in which all women have seven or eight children?"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 170807.0,
      "end_time": 174370.0,
      "text": "Or do we instead rely on the UN&#39;s account"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 174620.0,
      "end_time": 179125.0,
      "text": "that only one of Africa&#39;s 54 countries has a fertility rate as high as seven?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 179843.0,
      "end_time": 181585.0,
      "text": "Do we focus on the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 181610.0,
      "end_time": 185399.0,
      "text": "that infant mortality and life expectancy in Africa today"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 185423.0,
      "end_time": 188408.0,
      "text": "is roughly comparable to the US a hundred years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 188432.0,
      "end_time": 190987.0,
      "text": "or do we focus on progress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 191110.0,
      "end_time": 194242.0,
      "text": "the fact that Africa has cut infant mortality in half"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 194266.0,
      "end_time": 195535.0,
      "text": "in the last four decades"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 195559.0,
      "end_time": 199686.0,
      "text": "and has raised life expectancy by 10 years since the year 2000?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 201556.0,
      "end_time": 203365.0,
      "text": "These dueling perspectives"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 205327.0,
      "end_time": 206493.0,
      "text": "are all accurate."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 206517.0,
      "end_time": 208803.0,
      "text": "Well, aside from Macron&#39;s. He&#39;s just wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 208827.0,
      "end_time": 210692.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 210716.0,
      "end_time": 216256.0,
      "text": "But one version makes it easy to dismiss Africa as hopeless,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 216280.0,
      "end_time": 218534.0,
      "text": "while the other fuels hope that a billion people"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 218558.0,
      "end_time": 221120.0,
      "text": "can continue to make progress towards prosperity."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 223609.0,
      "end_time": 225213.0,
      "text": "The fact that Africans"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 225237.0,
      "end_time": 228649.0,
      "text": "do not have the luxury of turning their gaze elsewhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 228673.0,
      "end_time": 231164.0,
      "text": "the fact that we must make progress"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 231188.0,
      "end_time": 233656.0,
      "text": "or live with the consequence of failure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 233681.0,
      "end_time": 236713.0,
      "text": "are the reason we must continue to tell our own stories"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 236737.0,
      "end_time": 238547.0,
      "text": "and show our own images,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 238571.0,
      "end_time": 242628.0,
      "text": "with honesty and primarily to an African audience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 242652.0,
      "end_time": 245159.0,
      "text": "because the image that matters most"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 245183.0,
      "end_time": 249102.0,
      "text": "is the image of Africa in African imaginations."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 251931.0,
      "end_time": 254630.0,
      "text": "Now, honesty requires that we acknowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 254654.0,
      "end_time": 256670.0,
      "text": "that Africa is behind the rest of the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 256694.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259224.00000000003,
      "text": "and needs to move swiftly to catch up."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 260430.0,
      "end_time": 261966.0,
      "text": "But thinking of a way forward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 261990.0,
      "end_time": 264124.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like us to engage in a thought exercise."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 265370.0,
      "end_time": 267339.0,
      "text": "What if we could go back a hundred years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 267363.0,
      "end_time": 269925.0,
      "text": "say to the US in 1917,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 269949.0,
      "end_time": 273525.0,
      "text": "but we could take with us all the modern ideas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 273549.0,
      "end_time": 275869.0,
      "text": "innovations, inventions that we have today?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 277557.0,
      "end_time": 280137.0,
      "text": "What could we achieve with this knowledge?"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 280161.0,
      "end_time": 284707.0,
      "text": "How richly could we improve quality of life and living conditions for people?"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 286355.0,
      "end_time": 288752.0,
      "text": "How widely could we spread prosperity?"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 290594.0,
      "end_time": 292508.0,
      "text": "Imagine if a hundred years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 292532.0,
      "end_time": 295745.0,
      "text": "the education system had all the knowledge we have today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 295769.0,
      "end_time": 297451.0,
      "text": "including how best to teach."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 298778.0,
      "end_time": 301901.0,
      "text": "And doctors and scientists knew all we do"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 301925.0,
      "end_time": 305917.0,
      "text": "about public health measures, surgery techniques,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 305941.0,
      "end_time": 308986.0,
      "text": "DNA sequencing, cancer research and treatment?"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 309100.0,
      "end_time": 312804.0,
      "text": "If we had access then to modern semiconductors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 312828.0,
      "end_time": 315327.0,
      "text": "computers, mobile devices, the internet?"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 316151.0,
      "end_time": 317778.0,
      "text": "Just imagine."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 317802.0,
      "end_time": 322508.0,
      "text": "If we did, we could take a quantum leap forward, couldn&#39;t we."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 322532.0,
      "end_time": 326389.0,
      "text": "Well, Africa can take a leap of that magnitude today."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 327100.0,
      "end_time": 330163.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s enough untapped innovation"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 330187.0,
      "end_time": 334315.0,
      "text": "to move Africa a century forward in living conditions"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 334339.0,
      "end_time": 336805.0,
      "text": "if the will and commitment is there."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 337580.0,
      "end_time": 341394.0,
      "text": "This is not just a possibility; it&#39;s an imperative for Africa&#39;s future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 342375.0,
      "end_time": 345979.0,
      "text": "a future that will see Africa&#39;s population double"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 346300.0,
      "end_time": 349657.0,
      "text": "to two and a half billion people in just three decades,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 349681.0,
      "end_time": 353919.0,
      "text": "a future that will see Africa have the world&#39;s largest workforce,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 355190.0,
      "end_time": 359130.0,
      "text": "just as the idea of work itself is being radically reconsidered."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 360467.0,
      "end_time": 363107.0,
      "text": "Now taking the leap forward isn&#39;t that far-fetched."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 363131.0,
      "end_time": 366940.0,
      "text": "There are tons of examples that demonstrate the potential"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 366118.0,
      "end_time": 367474.0,
      "text": "for change in Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 369440.0,
      "end_time": 370448.0,
      "text": "Just 20 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 371782.0,
      "end_time": 374924.0,
      "text": "Nigeria had fewer than half a million working phone lines."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 374949.0,
      "end_time": 378210.0,
      "text": "Today it has a hundred million mobile phone subscriptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 378450.0,
      "end_time": 381975.0,
      "text": "and this mobile miracle is mirrored in every African country."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 381999.0,
      "end_time": 386693.0,
      "text": "There are over three quarters of a billion mobile phones in use in Africa today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 386717.0,
      "end_time": 390599.0,
      "text": "and this has spurred justified excitement about leapfrogging,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 390623.0,
      "end_time": 394567.0,
      "text": "about bringing the sharing economy, artificial intelligence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 394591.0,
      "end_time": 396821.0,
      "text": "autonomous machines to Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 398686.0,
      "end_time": 400631.0,
      "text": "And this is all promising,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 400655.0,
      "end_time": 402774.0,
      "text": "but we need to think about sequencing."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 404504.0,
      "end_time": 407193.0,
      "text": "Forget putting the cart before the horse."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 407217.0,
      "end_time": 409883.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t put the self-driving car before the roads."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 411502.0,
      "end_time": 416653.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 416677.0,
      "end_time": 420106.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a whole infrastructural and logical layer to innovation"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 420130.0,
      "end_time": 422424.0,
      "text": "that we take for granted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 422448.0,
      "end_time": 425220.0,
      "text": "but we have to triage for Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 425460.0,
      "end_time": 428276.0,
      "text": "because some of the biggest infrastructure gaps"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 428300.0,
      "end_time": 429888.0,
      "text": "are for things that are so basic"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 429912.0,
      "end_time": 432244.0,
      "text": "that Westerners rarely have to think about them."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 433772.0,
      "end_time": 435292.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s explore this."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 438800.0,
      "end_time": 441508.0,
      "text": "Imagine your internet access went off for a day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 443158.0,
      "end_time": 445159.0,
      "text": "and when it came back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 445183.0,
      "end_time": 447469.0,
      "text": "it only stayed on for three hours at a time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 447493.0,
      "end_time": 449754.0,
      "text": "with random 15-hour outages?"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 451270.0,
      "end_time": 452438.0,
      "text": "How would your life change?"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 453773.0,
      "end_time": 456193.0,
      "text": "Now replace internet access with electricity."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 458363.0,
      "end_time": 460911.0,
      "text": "Think of your fridges, your TVs, your microwaves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 460935.0,
      "end_time": 462537.0,
      "text": "just sitting idly for days."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 463389.0,
      "end_time": 467197.0,
      "text": "Now extend this nightmare to government offices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 467221.0,
      "end_time": 469807.0,
      "text": "to businesses, to schools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 470896.0,
      "end_time": 472860.0,
      "text": "to hospitals."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 474991.0,
      "end_time": 477531.0,
      "text": "This, or worse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 477555.0,
      "end_time": 480758.0,
      "text": "is the type of access that hundreds of millions of Africans"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 480782.0,
      "end_time": 481998.0,
      "text": "have to electricity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 483372.0,
      "end_time": 484522.0,
      "text": "and to water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 485687.0,
      "end_time": 486837.0,
      "text": "and to healthcare,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 487769.0,
      "end_time": 489220.0,
      "text": "and to sanitation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 489748.0,
      "end_time": 490974.0,
      "text": "and to education."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 492183.0,
      "end_time": 493389.0,
      "text": "We must fix this."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 494789.0,
      "end_time": 498780.0,
      "text": "We must fix this because ensuring widespread and affordable access"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 498804.0,
      "end_time": 501774.0,
      "text": "to decent infrastructure and services"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 501798.0,
      "end_time": 503472.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t just low-hanging fruit:"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 504183.0,
      "end_time": 506813.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s fundamental to achieving the hundred-year leap."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 508673.0,
      "end_time": 510539.0,
      "text": "And when we fix it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 510563.0,
      "end_time": 513427.0,
      "text": "we might find some unexpected benefits."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 515919.99999999994,
      "end_time": 518837.99999999994,
      "text": "One unexpected benefit of the mobile miracle"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 518863.00000000006,
      "end_time": 523600.00000000006,
      "text": "was that it led to what is perhaps the greatest cultural resurgence"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 523299.99999999994,
      "end_time": 525497.0,
      "text": "that Africa has seen in a generation:"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 525522.0,
      "end_time": 527814.0,
      "text": "the rebirth of African popular music."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 529162.0,
      "end_time": 533740.0,
      "text": "For musicians like P-Square,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 533980.0,
      "end_time": 534328.0,
      "text": "Bongo Maffin"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 535764.0,
      "end_time": 537110.0,
      "text": "and Wizkid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 537134.0,
      "end_time": 540849.0,
      "text": "mobile phones paved the path to local dominance"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 540873.0,
      "end_time": 542470.0,
      "text": "and global stardom."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 544634.0,
      "end_time": 548104.0,
      "text": "And the impact isn&#39;t limited just to music."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 548128.0,
      "end_time": 549539.0,
      "text": "It extends to film, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 550226.0,
      "end_time": 552814.0,
      "text": "Beautiful, engaging films"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 552838.0,
      "end_time": 555235.0,
      "text": "like these stills of \"Pumzi,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 555259.0,
      "end_time": 558500.0,
      "text": "\"Vaya,\" and \"I Am Not A Witch\" show."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 559515.0,
      "end_time": 562925.0,
      "text": "For while its external image might be dated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 562949.0,
      "end_time": 566300.0,
      "text": "Africa continues to evolve, as does African film."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 566920.0,
      "end_time": 570617.0,
      "text": "Now, every now and again, the rest of the world catches on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 570642.0,
      "end_time": 574952.0,
      "text": "perhaps with Djo Munga&#39;s hard-hitting \"Viva Riva!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 574976.0,
      "end_time": 577695.0,
      "text": "with Newton Aduaka&#39;s intense \"Ezra,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 577719.0,
      "end_time": 580465.0,
      "text": "or with Abderrahmane Sissako&#39;s poetic \"Timbuktu.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 581140.0,
      "end_time": 585472.0,
      "text": "With mobile, Africans are discovering more and more of these films,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 585496.0,
      "end_time": 590802.0,
      "text": "and what that means is that it really matters less in Kinshasa or Cotonou"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 590826.0,
      "end_time": 593494.0,
      "text": "what Cannes thinks of African film,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 593518.0,
      "end_time": 597167.0,
      "text": "or if those opinions are informed or fair."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 598113.0,
      "end_time": 600613.0,
      "text": "Who really cares what the \"New York Times\" thinks?"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 601565.0,
      "end_time": 606201.0,
      "text": "What matters is that Africans are validating African art and ideas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 606225.0,
      "end_time": 608567.0,
      "text": "both critically and commercially,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 608591.0,
      "end_time": 610599.0,
      "text": "that they are watching what they want,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 610623.0,
      "end_time": 613898.0,
      "text": "and that African filmmakers are connecting with their core audiences."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 615881.0,
      "end_time": 617526.0,
      "text": "And this is important."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 618480.0,
      "end_time": 621798.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s important because film can illuminate and inspire."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 622590.0,
      "end_time": 625806.0,
      "text": "Film can bring visions of the future to us here in the present."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 626800.0,
      "end_time": 629617.0,
      "text": "Films can serve as a conveyor belt for hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 630953.0,
      "end_time": 634108.0,
      "text": "And film can change perspectives faster than we can build roads."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 636171.0,
      "end_time": 638141.0,
      "text": "In just over a decade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 638165.0,
      "end_time": 640935.0,
      "text": "Nigeria&#39;s film industry, Africa&#39;s largest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 640959.0,
      "end_time": 645872.0,
      "text": "has taken the country&#39;s words and languages"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 645897.0,
      "end_time": 649723.0,
      "text": "into the vocabulary and imaginations of millions"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 649747.0,
      "end_time": 652740.0,
      "text": "in many other African countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 652990.0,
      "end_time": 654840.0,
      "text": "It has torn down borders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 654108.0,
      "end_time": 656986.0,
      "text": "perhaps in the most effective way since the Berlin Conference"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 657100.0,
      "end_time": 660129.0,
      "text": "sowed linguistic and geographic division across Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 660572.0,
      "end_time": 663960.0,
      "text": "Film does speak a universal language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 663120.0,
      "end_time": 665944.0,
      "text": "and boy, Nigerian film speaks it loudly."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 666845.0,
      "end_time": 669200.0,
      "text": "Making Africa&#39;s hundred-year leap"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 669440.0,
      "end_time": 672845.0,
      "text": "will require that Africans summon the creativity to generate ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 673916.0,
      "end_time": 678400.0,
      "text": "and find the openness to accept and adapt ideas from anywhere else in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 678424.0,
      "end_time": 680817.0,
      "text": "to solve our pervasive problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 681121.0,
      "end_time": 683740.0,
      "text": "With focus on investment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 683980.0,
      "end_time": 686454.0,
      "text": "films can help drive that change in Africa&#39;s people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 686479.0,
      "end_time": 689583.0,
      "text": "a change that is necessary to make the hundred-year leap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 689607.0,
      "end_time": 693241.0,
      "text": "a change that will help create a prosperous Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 693265.0,
      "end_time": 695931.0,
      "text": "an Africa that is dramatically better than it is today."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 697609.0,
      "end_time": 698760.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 698784.0,
      "end_time": 699934.0,
      "text": "Asante sana."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 699959.0,
      "end_time": 703920.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}